I've come across some issues with the changes to this from jquery 1.2.6 to the most receint, with safari calling find on a node of an XML doc returned by an axis call It calls this with an elem with nodeType=9 but it does not support documentElement and I get an error.

I'm not sure what is causing my issue, simple test cases seem to be fine.

I replaced this change which fixes it for me.

var isXML = function(elem){
    return elem.nodeType === 9 && ( !elem.documentElement || ( elem.documentElement.nodeName !== "HTML" ||
        !!elem.ownerDocument && elem.ownerDocument.documentElement.nodeName !== "HTML"));
};

John,
At jqcon in Boston, we discussed the performance differences between 
1.  $("#parent div");  
2.  $("div", "#parent"); 
3.  $("#parent").find("div"); 

