Tiny issue with emails not being remembered in failed login attempts.

Line 43 of sessions_controller.rb needs to say 
    @email = params[:email]
instead of fudgestudios/bort's:
    @login = params[:email]
Because that's the variable used in sessions/new.html.erb

Also, for the 'followers'/'following' m:n self-referential association on the User, doesn't it need the 'belongsTo' on one of the sides?

I think the better way to model m:n in this case would be through an explicit association class, something like 'SocialConnection' (or name whatever you like):

class SocialConnection {
   static belongsTo = [follower: User, followed: User]
   ...
}

class User {
   ...
   static hasMany = [followers: SocialConnection, followings:  SocialConnection]
  ...
}

I'm planning to implement this kind of a thing in Grails Crowd
